# Playbook: ghcr-publish

> Build a container image on the devbox and push it to a private registry
> (GitHub Container Registry) so a small VM can pull a ready image instead
> of building (which would OOM a 1 GB box). Generic template — replace the
> `{{PLACEHOLDERS}}`.

## When to use

- The app has a working `Dockerfile` and builds locally on the devbox.
- The VM is too small to build; it will pull the image at deploy time.

## Parameters

| Name | Example | Resolved from |
|---|---|---|
| `{{REGISTRY}}` | `ghcr.io` | provider |
| `{{OWNER}}` | `pl1n10` | GitHub username (lowercase in image ref) |
| `{{IMAGE}}` | `toto-mondiale` | repo / app name |
| `{{WRITE_PAT}}` | `ghp_...` | GitHub PAT, scope `write:packages` |

## Pre-flight checks (do these first, do not skip)

1. `docker build .` succeeds locally.
2. You have a **classic** PAT with `write:packages` (and `read:packages`).
3. The image ref owner segment is **lowercase** (`{{OWNER}}` lowercased).

## Steps

### 1. Log in to the registry

```bash
echo "{{WRITE_PAT}}" | docker login {{REGISTRY}} -u {{OWNER}} --password-stdin
```

### 2. Build and tag

```bash
docker build -t {{REGISTRY}}/{{OWNER}}/{{IMAGE}}:latest .
# optionally also tag with a version / git sha:
# docker tag ...:latest {{REGISTRY}}/{{OWNER}}/{{IMAGE}}:$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)
```

### 3. Push

```bash
docker push {{REGISTRY}}/{{OWNER}}/{{IMAGE}}:latest
```

### 4. Make the package private (first push only)

On GitHub > Packages > the package > Settings: set visibility **Private**.
Generate a **read-only** PAT (`read:packages`) for the VM/Watchtower to
pull with.

## Verify

- `docker pull {{REGISTRY}}/{{OWNER}}/{{IMAGE}}:latest` works from a clean
  `docker logout` + login with the read-only PAT.
- The package shows the new digest on GitHub.

## Common pitfalls

- **Uppercase owner**: `ghcr.io/Pl1n10/...` fails; image refs require
  lowercase. The GitHub username case does not matter for login, only
  for the image path.
- **Package defaults to private but unlinked**: link it to the repo and
  grant the read PAT, or Watchtower's pull 401s.
- **Re-tagging `:latest` without repushing**: Watchtower keys off the
  remote digest of `:latest`. Always push after building.

## What this playbook does NOT do

- Does **not** build on the VM (intentional).
- Does **not** deploy — that is `vm-provision-ansible` (the app role
  logs in with the read PAT and pulls).
- Does **not** set up CI; this is a manual devbox push in the MVP.
